uk.ac.kent.models.people

Class Employee

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.kent.models.people.Employee
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Director, Manager

    @Entity
public class Employee
extends Object
    Employee class represents all Employees working for the company. This includes Directors and Managers which are subclasses of Employee.

    To avoid data duplication, the Employee doesn't store her personal details. Instead, they are stored in PersonalDetailsRecord which is one of the documents that the system needs to handle.

    Therefore, modifying an Employee's details requires you to modify their PersonalDetailsRecord. The same applies to EmploymentDetailsRecord.

    Author:
    norbert
